%e A152138 We have a(1)=10 because a 3 X 10 chessboard was shown to be Hamiltonian by Bergholt in 1918, while there clearly are no Hamiltonian cycles on a 3 X 8 or 3 X 6 or 3 X 4 or 3 X 2 or 3 X odd.
